8. SigLIP 2 image + text encoders and bundled tokenizer (embeddings::siglip)

embeddings::siglip runs CoreML conversions of Google DeepMind's SigLIP 2
`siglip2-base-patch16-naflex` vision and text encoders (a shared 768-dim joint
embedding space), and BUNDLES that model's Gemma tokenizer into the compiled
crate via `include_bytes!` (exposed as
`coremlit::embeddings::siglip::BUNDLED_TOKENIZER`).

  8a) Encoder weights — google/siglip2-base-patch16-naflex. The crate ships NO
      model files; it loads a CoreML conversion produced LOCALLY from the official
      Google weights (the conversion/siglip recipes) — not consumed from any
      pre-uploaded artifact repo.

        Original model: google/siglip2-base-patch16-naflex
        https://huggingface.co/google/siglip2-base-patch16-naflex
        License: Apache-2.0 — preserve the Apache-2.0 attribution when
        redistributing the weights (or a binary bundling them).
        Attribution: Google DeepMind — SigLIP 2 (Tschannen et al., 2025).

        Converted from source revision (commit SHA):
        b53b807d3a2d5e2b3911292f2d69e5341cdc064c
        (model.safetensors SHA-256
        ac5f28bbdf92c0c1696ccbd3ce716426049cd67ad8045b66d0d938b0f9c8bbec).
        The converted artifacts are staged locally (gitignored); a public
        re-upload of them is a later owner decision and would add its own
        artifact-repo revision. The per-file SHA-256 of the converted bundles is
        pinned in tests/siglip/model_io.rs / tests/siglip/text_model_io.rs.

      As an Apache-2.0 work, a redistributor must retain the license and
      copyright notices AND STATE ANY CHANGES. Unlike a pure format conversion,
      the CoreML vision graph is RESTRUCTURED: the per-image position-embedding
      resize (a data-dependent antialiased F.interpolate) is lifted OUT of the
      graph to a host-side `position_embeddings` input that the Rust runtime
      computes per image. The attention lowering is the checkpoint's own
      scaled-dot-product attention as traced to CoreML, and the attention-pooling
      head is traced from the identical packed weights. The weight VALUES are
      unchanged (fp32 parity cosine 1.0000000 vs the stock model; the shipped fp16
      GPU arm is granite-class); the host-side position-embedding lift is the
      stated structural change.

  8b) Bundled tokenizer — siglip2-base-patch16-naflex Gemma tokenizer (via
      include_bytes!). Compiled into the crate, so any binary linking coremlit
      with the `siglip` feature redistributes it.

        Source: https://huggingface.co/google/siglip2-base-patch16-naflex
        Revision (commit SHA): b53b807d3a2d5e2b3911292f2d69e5341cdc064c
        Artifact: tokenizer.json
        SHA-256: 58a1696e79c9d97937389ed116f552a15c84811d7b8023918b86f4bc5775b1b0

      The artifact is the SigLIP 2 Gemma tokenizer configuration and vocabulary
      (256000 entries); it carries no model weights. It is distributed under the
      same upstream Apache-2.0 terms as the model; retain the license notice when
      redistributing it. (The committed `assets/tokenizer.json` is the real
      source-revision artifact, pinned by SHA-256 and proven byte-correct by the
      identity gate in tests/siglip/tokenizer_identity.rs.)

