9. CED AudioSet sound-event taggers (audio::ced)

audio::ced runs CoreML conversions of the four OFFICIAL public CED checkpoints
(Consistent Ensemble Distillation; arXiv 2308.11957; upstream RicherMans/CED),
one fp16 `mel → logits` graph per size. The crate ships NO model files; each
graph is converted locally by `crates/coremlit/conversion/ced/` and staged
gitignored under `Models/ced/ced-<size>/`.

        Original models — mispeech/ced-{tiny,mini,small,base}
        https://huggingface.co/mispeech/ced-tiny (…-mini / …-small / …-base)
        License: Apache-2.0 — preserve the Apache-2.0 attribution when
        redistributing the weights (or a binary bundling them).
        Attribution: Xiaomi Corporation — CED (Dinkel et al., 2023).
        Source revisions converted from (commit SHAs, also pinned in
        tests/ced/common/mod.rs and each size's Models/ced/ced-<size>/MANIFEST.json):
          tiny  ace276d29dd0bb3f3517b0fa8cf300738c409019
          mini  26c3ebcae85d4330f4fc26763f029539a3afcda0
          small 06bb40c5ec089e96867ebc5246be02441f4a71e4
          base  db3e14a8db4c21b56b165261c39649741a900e7f

      As an Apache-2.0 work, a redistributor must retain the license and
      copyright notices AND STATE ANY CHANGES. The CoreML graph is RESTRUCTURED
      from the identical `model.safetensors` weight VALUES: the `mel → logits`
      sub-forward is traced (the log-mel front-end is lifted to a Rust
      `MelExtractor`, so the graph starts at the mel, not the waveform), and the
      final `sigmoid` is dropped so the graph emits PRE-sigmoid logits (the
      caller applies the sigmoid). The weight values are unchanged (parity
      receipts: tests/ced/parity_logits.rs vs committed PyTorch fp32 goldens);
      these graph changes are the stated changes. An artifact-repo revision +
      per-file SHA-256 are pinned in tests/ced/model_io.rs.

      The committed golden corpus (tests/ced/fixtures/) is fully SYNTHETIC audio
      (deterministic sine / white-noise / silence generated by
      conversion/ced/scripts/_fixtures.py) — no third-party audio is
      redistributed. The 527 AudioSet class labels are provided by the
      `soundevents-dataset` crate (AudioSet ontology, Google).
